(3707, 844, 'awards', 'Grounds was awarded the RAIA Gold Medal in 1968 and knighted in the same year. In 1969 he was elected a life fellow of the RAIA. Jennifer Taylor has noted that Grounds combined rationalism and economical planning with a love of warm, natural materials Jennifer Taylor. His buildings, mostly houses, blended sensitively with their sites. There are several excellent examples of his work in Canberra.\r\n'),
